n altered form of this), itself probably a variant of   Filion   ‘little boy’. The surnames <i>Filiault</i> and <i>Filiau</i> are no longer found in France. Compare   Filyaw  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Filiol was born in 1310, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom as the son of Hugh Filiol and Mrs Hugh Filiol. He had at least 2 sons with Alice."},"et":{"1310–":"1310–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1311–Female":"1311–Surnud","1332–1381":"1332–1381","1334–Male":"1334–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","before 1310":"enne 1310","1334":"1334","1311":"1311","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","about 1334":"umbes 1334","1381":"1381","1280":"1280","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","of WOOLLAND,HORTON,DORSET,ENGLAND":"Woolland, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1310–":"1310–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1311–Female":"1311–Kuollut","1332–1381":"1332–1381","1334–Male":"1334–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1310":"ennen vuotta 1310","1334":"1334","1311":"1311","1310":"1310","1332":"1332","about 1334":"noin 1334","1381":"1381","1280":"1280","Dorsetshire, England":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Europe":"Eu